title: Report of March 8 in Oaxaca.
content:
The On March 8 in the city of Oaxaca, the Popular Women's Movement We join the workers' march called by the heroic Section XXII of the SNTE-CNTE in the framework of the International Day of Working Women. Comrades of the people, cooperative members, housewives, workers and women consciously we made the streets our own to the cry of Proletarian feminism destroys the patriarchy! next to the democratic teaching, and once again We take the opportunity to take a position in favor of heroic resistance National Palestine and the brave combatants of national liberation that They fight to throw out the Zionist invader. From the river to the sea, Palestine Expire!



Move From the Mother's Monument to the capital's Zócalo, in our A leaflet was made to call on all women to join this movement, explaining the differences between feminism and and bourgeois and petty-bourgeois feminism.

Also We participated with a speaker in the sound of the march. Our colleague set position emphasizing that "To women Gender unites us, but class separates us. We are working-class women and we make our own the historic programme of the revolutionary proletariat. Our agenda is not so-called gender ideology, but revolution proletarian" . As we went along, we realized that many shops and banks had already closed their doors and windows with wood or plywood; on arriving Around noon it was no surprise that the palace of the ignominy (government palace), as well as the kiosk were "armored" with sheets, timber and fences to prevent us from holding the rally at the End of the march. It is clear that this action speaks volumes about what is going on in the In reality, it is the Moreno government of Salomón Jara and his false "spring". The the closed-mindedness with which he has acted in more than a year of government, the repression and the lack of interest in resolving the various problems of the teaching profession and the Democratic organizations speak for themselves.



Before The response of the comrades was to recover and liberate this space removing the metal fence from our kiosk, which is part of the heritage of the and the people of Oaxaca, so that the message we were carrying would be heard throughout the country. and width of the square. So it was that once the kiosk was regained in the middle of the The working women were able to continue with the activities where they were called for us to continue the struggle for the defense of our rights and Above all, for the liberation of all humanity from the yoke capitalist-imperialist.

A Once the rally was completed, the anthem was sung we will win to continue with the forum "The woman in section XXII in the century twenty-one" where various presentations were made exposing the different problems faced by women education workers.

Do emphasis on the importance of the people's movement regaining meaning of this day, whose origin is undoubtedly of the workers' struggle and which is the working class is the only one that can liberate humanity from capitalism-imperialism, that patriarchy does not end with the hoaxes that call for "deconstruction" or "resignifying" things, or putting an end to the male sex. All of that is The verbiage of postmodernism that wants to hide the division of society into classes and the necessity of class struggle.

¡To the Patriarchy can only be ended when we sweep away private property of the means of production and the whole of humanity to transition to the glittering and golden communism!

We A call to all the women of the people and the comrades of the democratic movement to learn about proletarian feminism and to join the MFF.

Join the popular female movement!

Proletarian Feminism destroys the patriarchy!
